.TH "mpt3sas_get_port_by_id" 9 "mpt3sas_get_port_by_id" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mpt3sas_get_port_by_id \- get hba port entry corresponding to provided port number from port list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hba_port *" mpt3sas_get_port_by_id
.BI "(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc "  ","
.BI "u8 port_id "  ","
.BI "u8 bypass_dirty_port_flag "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioc" 12
per adapter object
.IP "port_id" 12
port number
.IP "bypass_dirty_port_flag" 12
when set look the matching hba port entry even
if hba port entry is marked as dirty.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Search for hba port entry corresponding to provided port number,
if available return port object otherwise return NULL.
